    "title": "RFC: Boost Process requires boost::filesystem when compiling with mingw",
    "body": "Working on \"Use std::filesystem. Remove Boost Filesystem & System\" #20744, I found an unfortunate [pitfall](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20744#issuecomment-946046666) -- `boost/process.hpp` depends on `boost::filesystem` when cross-compiling for Windows. It happens in Guix environment as well.\r\n\r\nThe goal of this issue is to discuss and find a solution to get rid of `boost::filesystem`.",
